Iranian students are ready to die for their country’s core program.
They formed a living shield.
A few hundred college students formed a living shield around a core object in Iran.
With this gesture, they wanted to demonstrate their support for their country’s core program before a possible Israeli attack.
The students had prayed in front of the object at noon Tuesday and then announced death to the United States and Israel.
A few hundred students from the University of Isfahan, Iran, formed a living sign on Tuesday around the nuclear technology center in Isfahan, where uranium is processed.
