The menu of a fat-addicted child: It does not have breakfast and eats sausage for dinner
More than a third of children ages 9 to 13 have problems with overweight, with 9 percent of all students and 5 percent of all children being overweight.
Recent surveys have shown that obese children mostly come from families with unhealthy lifestyles.
This shows once again how important to a person’s healthy development is the environment in which he grows up and are the examples that surround him.
On the tables of obese children, sausages are up to half as often on the table as in families where normal-weight children live.
More than 19 percent of overweight children had French fries for dinner on the day before the reconnaissance campaign under the motto "obesity is not a coincidence".
In families with fats, sports are not exactly one of the favorite occupations, but it also affects the majority of today’s students – only 15 percent responded that their parents find time for active exercise at least once a week.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place at the end of the school year last year, with nearly 900 children from primary schools across the Czech Republic surveyed.
This was already the second year of the action "Adiposity is not a coincidence", which is supported by the General Health Insurance and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12 thousand students from 4th and 8th grades have participated in the project.
Unhealthy diets and lack of exercise in the family are crucial factors that are responsible for the frighteningly increasing number of children who are overweight or even obese.
“Only half of the children surveyed, for example, claimed to eat breakfast-second lunch-vesper evening bread five times a day – one of the main prerequisites for a healthy diet,” according to one of the survey results.
No breakfast and sausage for dinner
Experts point out that even relative small things, such as the regular breakfast time of the family, are important for the healthy development of a child.
In the Czech Republic, only 23 percent of the students’ families have breakfast.
And - in most families, everyone eats breakfast on their own.
The worst thing was the finding that in every tenth family there is no breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the foundation of a healthy daily diet.
The survey test showed, among other things, that in the families of overweight children, unhealthy chips are consumed much more often.
And almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet lemonade every day (70 percent)
Although more than 40 percent of the children surveyed do sports, only less than half of their parents do – namely only 15 percent.
Create your own menu
Another part of the survey enabled selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to compose their own diet according to their appetite and opinion.
“What Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15 prefer in terms of diet is far from the ideal of a healthy diet.
Among her favorite dishes were many meals, meat dishes and of course sweets.
"Alarmingly, above all, the great popularity of sweet lemonades," is emphasized in the final report on this survey.
At lunch, the main dish, pasta was just ahead of poultry.
The children hardly liked legumes and the popularity of fish and vegetable dishes as lunch was very low.
Return to Health
At the same time, the survey also showed that the children are quite willing to change their eating habits if they get proper information.
"In the control group of respondents who completed the questionnaire after the enlightening lecture 'Adiposity is not a coincidence', there was a significant shift in preferences towards principles of healthy eating in many cases," the project's results indicate.
This was evident, for example, in the sweet limos, where many children began to give priority to ordinary water.
The children also crossed poultry or fish much more often in the questionnaire as the main dish of the day and were willing to eat less dumplings or sweet foods.
Professionals claim - a stylist must also be a good psychologist
In the introductory article on how stylists learn, I had a bit of a joke that that was a bit too much stuff to start with.
I didn’t know at all what was coming.
Lectures by three industry professionals, the clothing of problematic figures and a seminar about how the "in the square" works.
It's supposed to get worse.
The closer we get to the exam, the more information and practical tasks ahead of us.
But even if the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, it is still fully occupied.
This time we debated with director Alena (not a single man takes part in the course) how to attract a woman who does not have an ideally proportioned figure.
After all, these are most of us.
Some have a too short neck, the others a too young figure without proper curves and again others are chubby.
It is up to the stylist to visually laminated wide shoulders, to extend the neck or to conjure out the necessary curves.
We also got tips on how to dress a woman type like Jennifer Lopez – with a big bosom, wide hip and narrow waist – pretty and figuratively, without her being too provocative.
For example, if the difference between waist and hips is so great that the skirt or trousers really do not fit, you should at least get tailored to measure a piece.
You will not regret that, because well-fitting clothes are simply priceless.
In such a tailor-made skirt you feel much better than in one of the poles, which always slides up and down, sticks in the waist, etc.
Boylike figures, in turn, can allow themselves to wear clothing with folds, bumps, applications, embroidery or refining.
With this amount of information and figure types, I’m glad I have a whole week to let everything go through my mind thoroughly.
And yet I am afraid that, given the assigned homework, it is almost impossible to do.
Each of the students was assigned a celebrity for whom she was to come up with suitable outfits - daywear and evening dress.
In doing so, we should take into account the current appearance, the fashion style of the corresponding star and its figure type.
I'm supposed to "put on" Miranda Kerr, whom you may know from the Victoria's Secret campaign.
Inside I cheer, because that is much better for me personally than to dress Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who has probably increased to a hundred kilos in recent times (well, that’s a bit exaggerated), or even the young Selena Gomez.
We should cut the garments from magazines or search the internet, print them out and then edit them graphically.
In the "Moodboard", as the whole result is called, our very personal style and our relationship to graphic design will be expressed.
It is also very important to think about the graphical side of the styling.
The stylist not only physically attracts the models, but also designs the so-called product page in the journals (according to specific specifications, for example, trend handbags, coats, etc.).
Stylist and designer Mario Kamenák told us about this.
But that's not until Sunday.
This means that a stylist must have a good overall overview.
The Saturday lecture, filled with information about character types, was seasoned by three visitors from the industry:
by stylist Jan Pokorná, by fashion designer Jakub Polanka and by fashion photographer Ben Rená.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is illusion and that a stylist should be able to take advantage of it.
And skilled stylist can work with a single item of clothing in very different ways.
The magic word is variability.
For example, you can wear a trench coat over the jeans as usual, like a T-shirt or coat, but you can also wear it on the naked body, put on heel shoes and wear it as a dress.
It is enough to roll up the sleeves or the collar and the whole look looks completely different.
“Play with it,” he said.
But the most important advice for me was: “First you have to know the rules perfectly.”
“Only then can you hurt her,” Jakub said.
At last I realize why we have to break all these teachings, what can be combined with what and why, even if you often see something completely different in fashion journals.
Not to mention fashion shows.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I now know that a stylist must have prepared much more clothing variants than he ultimately photographs.
So you have to be prepared for a ten-page fashion story (say ten outfits) to style at least fifteen.
And also that the clothing in the photo in combination with other accessories sometimes looks very different than in reality.
All of this must be expected in the design of the outfit.
The fact that image and style sometimes make up half of the success, confirmed us also Jan Pokorn.
You just have to look at Madonna, a not exactly brilliant singer who made image and marketing a world star.
In the Czech Republic, one is more reserved for the services of a stylist.
Also, well-known personalities often consider this to be money thrown out (the main thing is that I bring something that I look like is secondary).
And if anyone of us can be styled, then we should expect that he or she is very likely to impose a completely different (smaller) size on us than he or she really needs.
Then you only need to google to determine with certainty that the tabloid press writes that the corresponding celebrity has returned to or decreased, etc.
Jan and Mario urged us on Sunday not to believe that a stylist just needs to focus on fashion and then “assemble” the outfit.
In his work, he must communicate primarily with the people he styles and he must be a skilled psychologist.
Evaluate people without embarrassment and stand by their opinion.
“If any manager orders us to look at her wardrobe and add some pretty pieces, then we can’t clear her whole wardrobe and say, ‘My God, that’s horrible.’
“You have to find at least a few commendable things to recommend what you can wear,” Mario says.
He also showed us very concretely what such a so-called "place bag" must include.
So such a bag that you put on the waist and in which you carry all the necessary proprietaries.
In addition to such clear things as scissors, unwinders for hair removal or safety needles, it also contains such utensils as a nylon thread (to help the stylist take photos of products, such as handbags or hats), special clips that are used to rip the back of the clothes if they are too big (pins or other clamps are not allowed, of course).
In order not only to listen, but also to try something practical, we learned how to put shoes under properly.
Even when photographing in the studio, where the floor is flat, you can damage the shoe sole, let alone the outside.
We sticked and we sticked...
With the scissors you must not even touch the shoes, so that you do not damage them.
So you have to be really clever.
Mario delighted me by praising my "creation" without restrictions.
This skill is not exactly my strength.
All of this was only the fraction of what we heard on the second weekend continuation course.
One thing has become clear to me in the meantime - to devote yourself to styling at a professional level is not a breeze.
V Need for Speed: "The Run" - the illegal race across America
Review
The original careless ride is made by a series of completely avoidable, dilettantious mistakes to the routine ride to the early shift.
Although it was possible to fulfill the ambitions to a large extent, what good is it if obviously no one wanted to do a little more?
Even before he came to the shop tables, the new part with the subtitle "The Run" raised high expectations.
He promised to move the already-old game series "Need for Speed" back into a new dimension and in the playable demonstration examples he actually seemed to be not just one of many action racing games.
We were also curious about the fitting passages where the main protagonist gets out of the car and continues on foot.
But as you are used to at NFS, in the end, a lot is different than you expected.
Sure - potentially they are quite decent arcade races, but overall, the game is diminished by some unnecessary bugs that have been present in this series for more or less a few years.
So it is actually no longer a mistake, but rather a sign of a basically incomprehensible laziness of the game developers.
The adventure begins very well.
First introduced to history, whose main character Jack has certain personal problems; the only solution seems to be to take part in an illegal race across America.
In San Francisco, on the west coast, you sit on the steering wheel - with the task of being the first in New York.
The basic idea includes a whole series of interesting elements.
The entire route is divided into ten stages and more than fifty individual races.
This means that each race is held on a different track and that the individual stages take place in a different, sufficiently different and interesting environment.
You don’t have the impression that game would always offer the same thing.
Some environments are still very nice to look at, although the technical level of the graphics does not go beyond that of the previous parts of the series.
So nothing world-moving.
But the drive through the desert, through autumnal scenery or high up through deep snowy scenery looks visually very pleasant.
From time to time, untypical elements bring a little variety to the individual races.
In the desert, for example, one is surprised by a desert storm that severely restricts sight.
In the mountains, you have to be very careful not to be spilled by an avalanche.
By the way, the individual races are quite well built in.
Only a few, but they are enough.
For a while you try to overtake the prescribed number of opponents (in principle a classic race), then you have time to overtake (classical race against the stopwatch), then you expect a personal duel with a single opponent.
And the police are also interfering, wanting to screw up the whole thing.
A novelty is passages in which Jack leaves the car.
This is more about certain interactive animations in which Jack flees from anyone and where the player has to help him by pressing the right button at the right moment.
So nothing complicated.
However, it is surprising that there are far fewer such passages in the game than you would expect (in concrete terms, only three).
Ultimately, this is more of an advantage, because at least this element has no chance of getting bored - it is one of the elements in the context of the above that make the game more varied.
The driving model moves into the footsteps of the previous parts.
That is, from today's point of view, it does not tear out trees, but on the other hand, one could not say that it would be bad.
If you are looking for realistic simulations, you have to look elsewhere.
But an action-packed racing model still lives up to the local driving model, although you could find better ones in the competition.
Until then, everything is in the best order.
Real problems only appear after a while.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not completely O.K.
A game of this kind is hardly expected to calculate complicated deformations and collisions, but if you have practically no idea of how the car behaves before an impact on any object, then obviously everything is not okay.
Typical example: When you make a close overtaking or passing by on accommodating cars, you "stroll" the other car only slightly in some places, but in other, almost identical situations you get into a spin and shoot wild pirouettes.
Or drive the car right to scrap.
Thanks to the restart system, this does not matter, but it is always annoying.
The restarts are solved in this way: if you have total damage or land far away from the track, then you throw the game back to the last point of reference of the track.
Only - in each race you have only five restarts.
When you have exhausted them, everything starts from the front.
So the restarts are more like a tool, in case something doesn’t work, but you shouldn’t rely on it.
Sometimes it doesn’t even help to restart, there’s nothing more than learning the critical section from your mind.
It is extremely unpleasant that the same things often happen in the same places.
Some curves you have to go through, for example, in a very specific way, otherwise you simply do not pass through.
Elsewhere, you will always find "civil" cars in the same configuration, whether you are first or fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations when you see the opponent passing by two cars in front of you, but until you get there, the cars are already in such a position that you have to drive them around or brake them.
And it doesn’t matter when you get there, everything is designed so that this situation always comes close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
In the whole game there are a few places where you are always overtaken by the same opponent at the same point and again here without regard to the timing.
The most crazy thing is to finish the game on the long bridge that you pass in the opposite direction.
The adversary must obviously overtake you here on the devil.
And if he is in front of you, of course he takes a look, so that you start driving your own car a few times in lumps.
Sure - you just want to make the game more exciting and exciting, but this intent is so clear that you quickly miss out on the joy of the game.
And that's a pity, because despite a simpler driving model, the game is quite entertaining and in some cases so action-packed that you almost don't know where your head is.
And in principle, it doesn't matter what "guilt" for it - the concept with fifty unique routes, the arrangement of the races in a way that can't be bored, or something completely different...
An unusual idea is also the change of carts during the races.
You should not miss the gas stations on the track, because here you can change the car, although in most cases the car you have is enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
The sports cars are well suited for the urban areas, the strong American sedans for the straight highways and exotic super sports cars for the technical journeys, for example on the serpentines in the mountains.
Hand in hand with the mode of the game history also goes the task mode (challenges) - i.e. the races in the individual locations you know from the history.
Here there are not only medals, but also experience points to gain for your own profile, which is common for the tasks (challenges) and the story.
To get to the higher level of the driver, various items have to be opened up: from the car to the backgrounds for the profile.
This is connected at the same time with the online Autolog function, which among other things compares your own results with those of other players and also provides further collective functions.
One of the other incomprehensible carvers is a situation in the last race of history.
Here you get by car to a subway tunnel (mostly), where you go on the tracks long in the dark (mostly).
On the tacho there are numbers between 150 and 200 km/h (in my opinion), but there suddenly comes a subway from behind and drives you uncompromisingly to scrap.
In our editorial team, we will probably argue for a long time whether this was a blackout of the game designers or whether the authors think us to be so stupid.
The technical side is nothing overwhelming but at least the overall visual impression is quite appealing in most cases and here and there even brilliant.
It is all the more annoying that in some exciting moments the refresh rate slows down and this is sometimes quite dramatic.
However, this applies in particular to accidents with a larger number of participants, where a continuous FPS is of no use anyway.
The sound playback is O.K. and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an effort to appeal to a scale as wide as possible rather young audience, a soundtrack a lá "of everyone something" - but who buys such a game because of the music?!
The overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run? The feelings are rather mixed.
If the game were not to be diminished by the above-mentioned totally unnecessary mistakes, we could have argued with the chest tone of conviction that The Run is the best piece of NFS in recent years.
But this is how the game looks somehow unfinished.
It’s a great pleasure in itself, but you should be prepared for these mistakes to come into your eyes with the power of airport headlights.
Concert of the "Students of the Velvet Revolution" with vocal ensembles of the Charles University
For the third time, Festa Academica offers the fusion of World Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution and music experience.
During the course of the festival, the twenty specialist and university choirs will present themselves.
The main focus of the festival is on the two concerts that take place on 17 November.
"Charles University has a big part in the festival."
"Among the participants is also the choir of the Faculty of Education and the Faculty of Humanistic Studies, and in the Festival Committee is also the Rector Václav Hampl," said Jakub Aloun, head of the organisational team.
The absolute highlight of the festival is the public concert of technical school choirs, which takes place on 17 November from 2 p.m. on the square in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The programme features the composition of the important Czech jazz player Karel Ráciska "Celebration Jazz Mass".
In the evenings, the concert "Students of the velvet revolution" (Studenty sametu) takes place in the gala rooms of the Volkshaus in Vinohrady, where also university choirs occur, choirs of the Charles University not excluded.
Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate World Student Day and commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present choral music at the highest level to the public and to promote creative cooperation among young people.
The main organizer is the association of Czech choirs in cooperation with the Johannes Kepler Gymnasium.
The patronage of the entire event was taken over by Bohuslav Svoboda, the mayor of the capital Prague, and Václav Hampl, the rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
In addition to festival concerts, the schedule also includes numerous music meetings, student happanings, matinees and other events.
For detailed information, please visit the website of the festival www.festaacademica.cz
EU Ambassador Vicenová:
The Czechs have the reputation of negativists and Eurosceptics
"The Treaty of Lisbon has made the balance between the individual institutions tangible."
I didn’t expect such a hard war to ignite.”
"It will take five or six years for the waves to smooth out and everyone to get used to their new role," Czech Ambassador to the European Union Milena Vicenová began her lecture at the Faculty of Law.
In the first part of her lecture, she showed how seriously she took the motto "understandable and open about Europe", in which she managed to describe the individual institutions of the EU and their mutual relations in such a manageable and understandable way that she could have envied so many lecturers from the Faculty of Law at Charles University.
Ms Vicenová also praised the new permanent chairman of the Council of Europe Herman Van Rompuy:
“At first, there was criticism that he was too inconspicuous – a gray official who wasn’t capable of such a role, but I have to say it left everyone breathless about how well he handled the matter.
He is a person who manages to listen patiently to twenty-seven member states, to communicate with them and, above all, has clear ideas of how to proceed with the EU.
She then explained the High Representative’s new position on foreign affairs and security policy in response to the question: Who is this really - the European Union? Which number should I call?", as an important step towards the unification and better legibility of EU policy towards countries such as China or India.
No one wants to ban us from our quartz oil hats.
Mrs Vicenová also devoted herself to the agenda according to which the European Union lived, lives and intends to live in the near future.
The Czech presidency two years ago was a success.
The Czechs would have mastered the financial crisis and the gas crisis and also hosted the Eastern Partnership Summit.
The government’s case during the presidency was described as a major negative, which had severely damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently full of work.
In the words of the ambassador, it was not only the presidency but also the subsequent crisis that has not yet been overcome.
And then there is the need to approve the EU’s seven-year budget, which makes things much more complicated precisely because of today’s economic situation.
Whether it’s going to be a lean and economical budget, which industries are given priority, which countries are more and which are less promoted – all of this is now on the agenda.
The ambassador also recalls her own slogans, with which she came to Brussels: "Understandable about Europe".
“If I don’t like something, it’s grayish abbreviations, foreign words, and technical jargon that no one understands.
How can I, as a citizen, really know if you are making up crooked or round cucumbers and bananas of different sizes in Brussels or if someone actually wants to ban us from quartels?
She would also have liked to use the EU’s soil to get more Czechs into European institutions.
Europe of two or different speeds in view
According to the EU ambassador, the Czechs have a reputation for being Eurosceptics, who perceive the negatives rather than the positives.
The weak representation of Czechs in European institutions is all the more annoying.
This is due to many factors, including the reluctance of our candidates, their inability to write motivational letters and, last but not least, the weak support of the Czech side.
In addition to the successful Czech presidency, it also highlighted the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group, the so-called V4.
“Believe me, when a Pole or Hungarian comes to me and a Slovak is around, the Frenchman next to me says, ‘Hey, what are your heads together – is that your V4 again?’
According to Mrs Vicenové, the EU expects in the future, above all, tough rules for the budgetary policies of the Member States.
As much more real, as a "European federation", she sees the concept of a Europe of two or even different speeds.
“We have here the countries of the eurozone and the countries away from the eurozone.
“We have the Schengen area and we already have the institute of enhanced cooperation.”
“For the first time, it was said that only those countries that want to work together and those that don’t want to work together should stay away.”
"There will be more and more such institutions, which will ultimately lead to a strong 'Europe of different speeds'," Vicenová expects.
In this regard, she also acknowledged the role of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuyes in enforcing the principle that all issues must be discussed by all Member States and not only by the countries of the euro area with an impact on the EU as a whole.
Brand Story:
Innovator IBM enters the second century of its existence
If you wanted to look for a suitable word that most accurately characterizes IBM’s strategy, that would probably be the word “longevity.”
For the general public, IBM is synonymous with technological revolution, known as a modern enterprise, although a century has passed since its inception.
The foundation for this longevity was already laid by her first boss - visionary Thomas J. Watson sen.
