Here is a tip on how to proceed: gently cut out this page and make it your bookmark.
You will get to know these people very well in England's romance story, and these main characters will function as your GPS, as a lighthouse in those few moments when you, like England's men and women, are lost in the fog of war and deprived of your illusions.
Peter Englund is a Swedish historian and journalist.
He is also the new permanent secretary of the Swedish Academy, which awards the Nobel Prize in Literature.
He has written an unusual book that he does not misrepresent as “a work of anti-history.”
It contains only a few big names, important contracts or famous battles. There are hardly any ambassadors, raging reporters or discussions about tactics and equipment.
It is less a book about what happened, he explains, but rather "a book about how it was." It is about "feelings, impressions, experiences and moods".
