The Queen inaugurated the fifth World Summit on Microcredit in Valladolid yesterday. She was convinced that there was “no doubt” that these types of business would be “absolutely essential” to achieve the Millennium Goals set by the United Nations by 2015 and “especially the goal of limiting the number of people living with incomes of less than one dollar a day.”
Spain "continues to work" on expanding the beneficiary network "to the last corner of the world and it is doing this task responsibly," noted Queen Sofia, who hopes that the initiatives and contributions from the summit, which will last until Thursday, "will guarantee the creation of new capacities and better opportunities for the poorest, and especially for women", as the main beneficiaries of these loans.
